description.plain:
Khalick Antonio Caldwell (born January 1, 1996), better known as Stunna 4 Vegas, is a rapper from Salisbury, North Carolina. He is a frequent collaborator of fellow Carolina rapper DaBaby.

Stunna started rapping as early as 2014 but didn’t release his first mixtape, Boot Up, until January 2017. He continued to release more mixtapes during the rest of 2017 and into 2018.

Stunna gained some attention in the hip-hop scene with tracks like “No Reason” featuring Jimmy Wopo and “Questions,” and this caught the eye of DaBaby, who made a guest appearance on Stunna’s biggest track to date, “Animal.”

After this, Stunna was signed to DaBaby’s label Billion Dollar Baby Entertainment and was featured on his October 2018 track “4X.”

Stunna soon signed with Interscope Records and released his debut studio album, BIG 4X, under the label.

His second studio album, RICH YOUNGIN, was released on January 17, 2020.

Stunna 4 Vegas teams up with DaBaby on “Animal” – a track that discusses their “crazy” personalities, sexual prowess, and material possessions.

This track serves as the first collaboration between the two friends, although they have collaborated numerous times since.

songs.title: Ashley

description.plain:
“Ashley” is a track that reunites DaBaby and Stunna 4 Vegas and appears on Stunna’s BIG 4X. On the track, the rappers exchange bars about their newfound fame, hood origins, and sexual prowess.

This track marks the sixth collaboration between the two friends and the second on this album, following the success of Stunna’s September 2018 track, “Animal,” and DaBaby’s October 2018 track, “4X,” DaBaby’s “Fan Freestyle,” DaBaby’s March 2019 track, “Joggers,” and “Sticks,” which appears earlier on this album.
